We want to find the matrix that corresponds to a dilation centered at the origin with scale factor $-3.$

Dilation matrix formula:

\begin{bmatrix} a & b \\ c & d \end{bmatrix}

= \begin{bmatrix} scale\ factor \times cos(\theta) & scale \ factor \times sin(\theta) \\ -scale\ factor \times sin(\theta) & scale\ factor \times cos(\theta) \end{bmatrix}.

Since we're dilating centered at the origin with scale factor $-3$ and we want the dilation matrix, 
and since no special direction has been specified we'll let $\theta = 0.$

With $\theta=0$, $\cos \theta=1$ and $\sin\theta=0,$

But $scale \ factor=-3$.

Therefore, our matrix is:

\begin{bmatrix} a & b \\ c & d \end{bmatrix}

= \begin{bmatrix} -3\times cos(0) & -3 \times sin(0) \\ -(-3) \times sin(0) & -3 \times cos(0) \end{bmatrix}

= \begin{bmatrix} -3\times 1 & -3 \times 0 \\ -(-3) \times 0 & -3 \times 1 \end{bmatrix}

= \begin{bmatrix} -3 & 0 \\ 0 & -3 \end{bmatrix}

Answer:

\boxed{\begin{bmatrix} -3 & 0 \\ 0 & -3 \end{bmatrix}}

