The formula for reflection of a vector $\mathbf{b}$ over a vector $\mathbf{a}$ is given by:

\begin{align*}
2\text{ Projection of }\mathbf{b}\text{ onto }\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b}
\end{align*}

where "Projection of $\mathbf{b}$ onto $\mathbf{a}$" means, the projection of $\mathbf{b}$ onto $\mathbf{a}$.

The projection formula is 

\begin{align*}
\frac{\mathbf{b} \cdot \mathbf{a}}{\|\mathbf{a}\|^2}\mathbf{a}
\end{align*}

Now substitute in our values.

\begin{align*}
\mathbf{b} &= \begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix} \\
\mathbf{a} &= \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} \\
\|\mathbf{a}\|^2 &= 1^2 + 3^2 = 1 + 9 = 10 \\
\mathbf{b} \cdot \mathbf{a} &= 0\times 1 + 4 \times 3 = 12 \\
\end{align*}

projection onto a =
$\begin{pmatrix} \frac{12}{10} \times 1 \\ \frac{12}{10} \times 3 \end{pmatrix}$
$\\
= \begin{pmatrix} \frac{6}{5} \\ \frac{18}{5} \end{pmatrix}\\
$

\\$2$ times the projection onto $\mathbf{a}$ is \\$2\text{ Projection of }\mathbf{b}\text{ onto }\mathbf{a} = 2 \\
\begin{pmatrix} \frac{6}{5} \\ \frac{18}{5} \end{pmatrix} \\
\\= \begin{pmatrix} \frac{12}{5} \\ \frac{36}{5} \end{pmatrix} \\$

Reflection of b onto a \\$ 2\text{ Projection of }\mathbf{b}\text{ onto }\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b} \\$ is

\begin{align*}
& 2\text{ Projection of }\mathbf{b}\text{ onto }\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b} \\
